content: TLDR - Absolutely spectacular sound design. - Alright UI design. - Sleep timer sometimes works. Sometimes doesn't.   A pretty okay ambiance/rain sound app. I use it as my daily driver so rain sounds, however I've encountered a couple issue. The biggest and most important one for me is that the sleep timer only sometimes works. Sometimes the rain just keeps going throughout the night draining my battery the whole night. The other issue is just (comparatively) bad UI design. Some menus and stuff feel awkwardly tucked away. But it's pretty acceptable! However the sound quality is truly amazing compared to any app I've tried on the market. There is so much more depth to the sound. Obviously the better the sound system the better the experience. But it is more dynamic than anything I've heard. Having the rain naturally grow louder and softer as time goes on.
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback. We'll look into these issues and try to improve things in future releases.

It's easily worth the low price and I LOVE that it works ON TOP of the music I'm playing. One other thing that I love is that even if I stop my music, the rain keeps going. I only have one gripe and two suggestions. My gripe is that sometimes the rain sound will stop after 20 minutes or an hour, while other times, it'll play all night. Even when I don't have the sleep timer on, it'll still randomly stop. I've gone through my settings and allowed background apps to continue running, so I'm not sure why it stops. One suggestion is to add a panel for rain against a window pane. My other suggestion is a volume slider. When I play music with the rain, sometimes the music will nearly drown out the rain sounds and I'll barely hear the rain app. Since the rain volume turns down with my music, there's no way to avoid this.   All in all a very very great app for those of us who enjoy rain sounds.

For as feature light as this app is, it has a lot of bugs. Features are: independent volume sliders for rain and thunder, a button to open a music player of your choice (and display the Now Playing information for the selected app), a sleep timer that's either off or set to 1 hour with no visible count down, and a play/pause button to start/pause the rain.  I've been going to sleep with the sleep timer and a short playlist playing. More than once I've woken up after several hours and realized the rain was still going after the specified 1 hour timer.  Other times the app with simply not play until the play/pause button is toggled a few times. Sometimes it'll keep playing rain sounds if the Home button is pressed (expected) and sometimes it won't.  Sometimes you can pause the rain and leave the app with the phone's Back button and the app will close (expected) and sometimes it wont.

I purchased this software, despite the ridiculously high price tag, in the hopes that this would be the be all - end all of storm simulation. While the quality of the individual loops are good, the overall framework for playing these effects and the editing for the effects are awful. Each of the rain effects vary wildly in volume, beyond the point of "this rain sounds closer than that rain" and none of the samples crossfade with each other, making it sound like it literally is playing one sound file after another. The thunder samples have no low end to them at all and are repetitive (playing through an accurate and high end sound system)  I've emailed the developer a couple of times telling him or her these things, even offering to help with improvements, since Sound Design is what I do for a living, but there has only been 1 update to the software since I purchased it (pretty much the day it came out) and it didn't address any of these issues.  This has so much wasted potential. Don't purchase. I wish I could get my money back.

I really like this app. It's expensive, however I work in a highly stressful environment with poor living conditions currently. At night it is very loud, so I like to wear noise isolating headphones and relax for a while. The dynamic rain noise generated by the app (and website) is much more refreshing than my previous nature noise soundtracks, and with the music combination capabilities, I can even merge my current soundtracks with rain. Yes!  Current bug for me is that when I hit 'pause' or even end the app, etc, the noise starts up again after maybe half an hour. Finally did something (forget, it was 4AM)  and it shut off. Aside from the small bugs here and there, this is a wonderful app for those who travel or experience high levels of stress and need to wind down after a tough day.

Currently a somewhat buggy, barebones atmospheric sound app priced a bit too high for my liking, but with hands down the best rain sound effects on Play. With more options the app has the opportunity to be amazing.

Fantastic application. I've been looking for a good rain/mood music application for a long time on Android and I think I've finally found it.  The sound quality is unmatched by the multitudes of others applications I've tried and the interface is simple and clean. It has no problems with looping or anything of that sort even on the latest builds of Android 4.x ICS and it's very stable and smooth.  This is basically what I've been waiting for in a rain app since I left iOS 1-2 years ago. 5 stars. I have a few points of feedback though.  - It'd be great if we could select the rain type to play continuously if we like one. I'm partial to 'rain on a tin roof', but Rainy Mood just cycles. - I'm sure some people will want to be able to adjust the sleep timer past 1 hr. - This is petty, but I do feel like the icons in the main 'control box' could look a little cleaner and nicer, but that's just personal preference.  Thanks for the great app guys!
